Dedication to the Game :
------------------------

Switching between lessons and coding sessions, or trying out other applications, isn't always easy.

For this example,
I'm offering a linear TI-89 script, this is a configuration, complete as possible to the factory settings, safer than Mem-Menu.

You can easily remove useless settings, change every settîngs to your own, cut in multiple cfg files !

(I have personnaly, 5 different configuration files !)

By creating your own cfg, you will be able to quickly return to your personal settings.

I hope you'll find useful to insert `cstmkill()` or his code, somewhere between your own settings.

Remark:
-------
This isn't a tutorial; I'm counting on your inspiration to optimize all the modes you need (e.g., Graph/Table Sync). Then you can move on to string manipulation ( my favorite :) ) . (FnCheck)





Added : Graph / Table Synchronization
